…Says 8.00 p.m. to 6.00 a.m. Curfew Still Enforce By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja  (Sundiata Post)  –The Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 on Monday extended the ease of lockdown in Abuja, Lagos and Ogun by two weeks. Boss Mustapha who made the announcement said that lifting the lockdown at this stage will make nonsense of the achievement recorded. Speaking today during the daily media briefing in Abuja, Chairman of the Presidential Task Force on Coronavirus Pandemic and Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Mr Boss Mustapha the decision became necessary because of the increasing number of cases in the country. He said the extension which will begin on Tuesday will last till the first week of June. He also said the 8.00 p.m. to 6.00 a.m. curfew put in place by the government would still be in place. Details later….. •President Muhammadu Buhari In view of the rising cases of COVID-19 in the country, President Muhammadu Buhari, would on Monday extend the lockdown in Abuja as well as Lagos and Ogun States for another two weeks. The president would however relax some of the restrictions on essential business activities by… April 26, 2020 In "News" The Presidential Task Force (PTF) on COVID-19, has explained how the easing of lockdown in Lagos, Abuja and Ogun state will be implemented. President Muhammadu Buhari had on Monday, April 27, approved the gradual easing of lockdown in the two states and the FCT as from Monday, May 4. He… April 30, 2020 In "News" Two Senior Advocates of Nigeria (SANs), Dr Olisa Agbakoba and Ebun-Olu Adegboruwa have disagreed on Monday’s broadcast of President Muhammadu Buhari on the way forward towards curtailing the spread of the coronavirus pandemic. While Dr Agbakoba, a former President of the Nigerian Bar Association (NBA) lauded President Buhari over new… April 28, 2020 In "News"